name: Loetje Amsterdam ZuidAs
description:
Even lekker uit eten aan de Zuidas in Amsterdam? Kom Loetje doen!

Midden in het zakelijk hart van Amsterdam vind je ons in een licht en modern restaurant aan het water. Een populaire plek waar je heerlijk kunt borrelen en eten. Vanaf ons terras heb je een mooi uitzicht over de gracht van de Boelelaan. Perfect voor een zakenlunch of om de week gezellig af te sluiten met vrienden of familie.

Iedereen weet; de beste biefstuk van Amsterdam eet je bij Loetje. Deze serveren we al ruim 45 jaar op onze eigen no-nonsense manier, in jus en met zacht witbrood. Daarnaast is de steak tartaar een echte blijmaker, maar ook onze kipsate, hamburger en biefstuk 0.0 zijn succesnummers op de menukaart.

Tot snel bij Loetje ZuidAs!

name: The Harbour Club
description: In het hart van Oud-Zuid, daar waar de vijf Amsterdamse grachten samenkomen, vind je The Harbour Club Amsterdam Zuid. Een uniek restaurantconcept gelegen op een historisch stukje Amsterdam aan het water en gevestigd in het viersterren Apollo Hotel Amsterdam, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel. Hier geniet je van internationale allure, een chique, maar ontspannen sfeer en buitengewoon fantastisch eten. Neem plaats in het ruime restaurant met prachtige kleuren, stoffen en wandschilderingen. Of geniet op het zonnige terras met uitzicht op de gracht en voorbij varende boten.

name: The Traveller
description: The Traveller bevind zich in de Rivierenbuurt in Amsterdam-Zuid. Het fraaie en opvallende horecapand ligt aan het Europaplein, pal naast de Rai. The Traveller Zuid is hier een levendige ontmoetingsplek voor omwonenden, ondernemers, studenten en congresbezoekers. Kom binnen op elk moment van de dag want wij zijn open van 's ochtends vroeg tot 's avonds laat. Op de menukaart staat een mix van de lekkerste traditionele wereldgerechten, bereid in onze hypermoderne open keuken. Veel gerechten zijn bedoeld om met elkaar te delen, zoals dat in verschillende landen de eetcultuur is. Daarnaast is ook de uitgebreide drankenkaart internationaal getint met "speciaal" bieren, wijnen uit alle continenten, spannende cocktails, G&T's en much-much more.

This area has a lot of big office buildings and is not as lively when they are closed. There is enough payed parking in a short walk distance, no valet parking. The restaurant itself looks modern, serene. Staff is friendly and as soon as we were seated the first small bites arrived. Most of the menu is based around vegetables because the restaurant has its own garden at the busy Zuidas. We had a three course lunch menu with the first two courses being vegetables and the final course fish. I found the taste sometimes a bit blend. Missing not only seasoning but an exciting sauce to get a bit more flavor differences out of the vegs.

The restaurant has a terrace and staff is friendly and knowledgeable. The wine was great and they also have a juice menu. All in all for me the rating gets three stars because of the combination between the (personal) bit blend flavors and price. Definitely a nice experience and a dream for vegans! It's been years since my first time here, Bakers & Roasters is one of Amsterdam institutions for brunch/lunch. I ordered the veg brekkie (price: 18 euro).
The space is pretty narrow, and the tables are very close to each other. Most of the times there is some waiting time, but the service is very fast, and you are in and out within the hour. Tap water is served immediately (nice touch! Many Amsterdam places will  try to sell you overpriced bottled water).

The food is nice, in my case, simple and well cooked (poached eggs were perfectly cooked). I liked the spicy jelly in combination with the dish.
If I need to find a flaw: probably the size of the coffee cup, quite small for my preferences, I love a large cup of coffee vs. the 120ml size of their flat white.

name: Cafe Loetje
description:
De plek waar het ruim 45 jaar geleden allemaal is begonnen: Loetje Amsterdam Cafe aan de Johannes Vermeerstraat in Amsterdam Zuid. In 1977 door Ludwig 'Loetje' Klinkhamer opgericht als biljartcafe. Toen de inmiddels beroemde ossenhaasbiefstuk op het menu kwam, verdwenen de biljarttafels al snel naar de achtergrond en werd hier geschiedenis geschreven.

Tegenwoordig kun je nog steeds elke dag bij Loetje Amsterdam Cafe genieten van de lekkerste biefstuk van Amsterdam. Bij ons geniet je van het vertrouwde biefstukreceptuur en het warme Loetje DNA. Bij ons zit je naast deze klassieker ook goed voor vis, vegetarisch en overheerlijke toetjes. Zien we je snel?

Team Loetje

name: Dignita Vondelpark
description: We've been conjuring up delicious brunches and exceptional coffee since August 2015. We're focused on serving you the freshest food with every attention paid to detail; our philosophy is to handcraft every menu item from scratch using free-range and locally sourced ingredients where possible. Whether you're in Amsterdam or The Hague, we're your go-to spot for a satisfying brunch, lunch, or breakfast experience. Our restaurants are situated in prime locations: in the heart of Amsterdam Zuid, nestled amongst the oasis of the Hoftuin, right in the centre of Amsterdam; near Amsterdam Westerpark; or in The Hague's vibrant Zeehelden neighborhood.

The Cilbir poached eggs caught my eye with their Turkish-inspired twist, adding an interesting flavor profile to the meal. To round things out, I enjoyed a cup of coffee and a refreshing jar of juice.

That said, the quality was certainly there, and I appreciated the effort to incorporate diverse influences into the menu.

One thing to note is the restaurant's size. Dignita Vondelpark is quite small and tends to get packed quickly. I'd strongly recommend making a reservation to avoid disappointment.

name: Oliver's
description:
OLIVER'S first opened its doors in 2007 and quickly became known as one of the best restaurants and lunchrooms in Amsterdam Zuidas.

Guests praise our price-quality ratio, our hospitality, the no-nonsense cosiness and the fact that everyone feels at home with us. We believe in fast, fresh, homemade food from all over the world.
We hope to welcome you soon in the center of Amsterdam Zuidas at Claude Debussylaan 78.

name: Aubergini Restaurant
description: Aubergini is a unique homemade concept inspired by Mexican, Italian, and Japanese kitchens. As an inclusive cuisine we offer organic meat, chicken and fish as well as glutenfree and vegan options. We use daily fresh and organic (where possible) ingredients to make Burgers, Bowls, Wraps, Sandwiches en drinks. We make pretty much everything ourselves from Low fat Beef Burgers to pure Mineral Water. Connect with us via our website. Looking forward to welcoming you.

name: The Burger Room
description:
We are that Burger Restaurant and Cocktail Bar inspired by The Wizard Of Oz located in the heart of Amsterdam's Fashion and Museum District.
We serve top-notch burgers made of prime beef and signature cocktails stirred and shaken by our mixologists.

*** CHILDREN ARE WELCOME FROM THE AGE OF FIVE ***
*** Dogs are not welcome regarding hygiene reasons ***

See you soon, and don't forget:
Oz is just around the Corner!

What a pleasant surprise!!! The menu includes a choice of Angus or Wagyu beef. We ordered Angus... in our minds Wagyu seems better reserved for a steak.

The food was phenomenal! Some of the best burgers of our lifetimes! I ordered the Back to Kansas burger (Black Angus beef, cheddar cheese, the Burger Room sauce, romaine lettuce, no tomato), Oz Rings, and the Yellow Brick Road cocktail (their own proprietary Limoncello). My daughter ordered The Scarecrow burger (Black Angus, bacon, cheddar cheese, carmelized onion, pickle, remaine, no tomato) with fries, and the Kan Niet Heksen cocktail (the burger rum blend, ginger, spekkoek, and lime). And for dessert, the Melted Wicked Witch Freakshake - not for the faint at heart!

While you are there be sure to follow the yellow brick road to the bathroom in the lower level. The Oz theme continues with green and gold sinks, mirrors and walls. Try not to get caught up in the continuously running movie while gawking at the Oz memorabilia.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURua2RHOHlRRRAB","rating":5,"name":"C Y","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106271181044276475223?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Highly recommended!
We visited this amazing restaurant on a Sunday evening. We throughly enjoyed the 9 course menu at the chef's table, each course was was full of flavour and well presented. The service was super attentive, and the cocktails were amazing! The best version of expresso martini we've ever had!

name: Lokaal van de Stad
description: Op de hoek van Heemstedestraat en Westlandgracht zit Lokaal van de Stad. Dit cafe-restaurant telt 2 verdiepingen en is daarmee uitermate geschikt om goed te borrelen en lekker te ontbijten, lunchen en dineren. Geniet van de vele verschillende biertjes of heerlijke wijnen naast een van de gerechten uit onze wereld keuken.

While the food was enjoyable, the service left much to be desired.

Let's start with the positives. The food at Lokaal van de Stad was undeniably delicious. I tried their seafood risotto, and the flavors were rich and well-balanced. The seafood was fresh, and the dish was cooked to perfection. Additionally, their dessert menu offered a variety of tempting options, and the chocolate lava cake I ordered was decadent and satisfying.

However, my dining experience was marred by the subpar service. The staff seemed disorganized and inattentive, often forgetting to bring requested items and taking an excessively long time to attend to our table. It was frustrating to have to repeatedly ask for water refills and wait extended periods for our orders to be taken.

Moreover, the lack of communication between the waitstaff and the kitchen resulted in some mistakes with our orders. One of our appetizers arrived much later than the others, and one of the main courses had to be sent back because it was undercooked. These issues could have been avoided with better coordination and attention to detail.

Despite the service shortcomings, I must commend the kitchen staff for their culinary skills. The food itself was the saving grace of my dining experience at Lokaal van de Stad. However, the lack of attentive service left a sour taste in my mouth and prevented me from fully enjoying what could have been an outstanding meal.

In conclusion, while Lokaal van de Stad showcased culinary prowess, the disappointing service experience significantly impacted my overall impression. I hope they address the service issues and improve their front-of-house operations to match the quality of their food.","published_at":"a year ago","published_at_date":"2023-06-28T16:11:10","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":5,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOk-d06sBpQT4EKzMZ1caTKrJ-6Rkr5m2tSgy8M=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipO7yBHPUFc4C1XvHX797geul8IlcDxmSXfcFXlq=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP2FhOdT1rFZNKvSAEWWxduJfMH0U4bnTMrMi5x=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMUguFak_n3dKS-vRhg1IZ9ickLaO7xBac7zlBt=s1024"]}]

name: Poppy's Restaurant Amsterdam Zuid
description: Poppy's Restaurant Amsterdam Zuid is our second cozy and colourful restaurant and cafe in the city. We serve our eye catching and internationally inspired dishes with the tastiest and best looking cocktails in Amsterdam. Besides lovely dinners, our restaurant welcomes you for a cup of coffee, high tea, brunch or lunch in Amsterdam Zuid. Drop by to enjoy a wide array of drinks, from fresh juices to cocktails and wines to combine with some irresistible snacks. Whether you're looking for a restaurant in Amsterdam Zuid, a cocktailbar in Amsterdam Zuid or craving our famous Amsterdam high tea, Poppy's is here for you! Our restaurant and cafe is highly suited for events such as bridal events, babyshowers, family gatherings and birthday parties.

The octopus was well-cooked, but we personally did not like the sauce.

The fish, the coquille and the steak tartar were good, but not good enough for us to come back.

name: Restaurant Sardegna
description:
In the characteristic Cornelis Schuytstraat in the Old South you will find restaurant Sardegna. Inside or on the royal terrace with heating, for lunch or dinner, for business or private gatherings in a cosy Italian ambience.
Our products and ingredients come directly from Italy, and the pastas are made by hand in-house. We invite you into our Italian atmosphere for pizza, pasta, carne (meat) or pesce (fish).
Also try our beautiful Italian house wines, or choose from our specially selected wine menu.

We'd love to see you soon!

name: Cafe Garcon
description: Cafe Garcon opent zijn deuren in Amsterdam Oud-Zuid! Geinspireerd door de Franse keuken, zeven dagen per week open voor lunch, diner en apero. Kom culinair dineren of 'pour un cafe' op ons verwarmde terras en geniet van de Franse sferen. A bientot!

name: Spaghetteria
description: Geniet van een authentieke Italiaanse ervaring bij Spaghetteria Caffe, een van de beste restaurants in Amsterdam. Of u nu op zoek bent naar een traditioneel Italiaans diner of een snelle lunch in Amsterdam, Spaghetteria Caffe is de perfecte plek. Proef de heerlijke pasta's, bereid met verse, lokale ingredienten. Dit restaurant is een favoriet onder de lokale bevolking en toeristen voor zijn authentieke eten en gezellige sfeer. Ervaar de ware essentie van Amsterdamse eetgelegenheden terwijl u geniet van de heerlijke smaken van de Italiaanse keuken. Dus waar wacht u nog op? Bezoek vandaag nog Spaghetteria Caffe en ontdek waarom het wordt beschouwd als een van de beste Italiaanse restaurants in Amsterdam.

name: TEN good food cafe
description: Beleef de ultieme kunstervaring bij TEN Good Food Cafe, de sociale ontmoetingsplek in het Stedelijk Museum Amsterdam! Dit hippe, maar toegankelijke cafe voelt als een gezellige huiskamer waar je de hele dag welkom bent. Geniet van het ruime terras, dat in de zomer deels overdekt is, en begin je dag ontspannen met een heerlijk ontbijt. Of praat na over de indrukwekkende tentoonstelling van grootmeesters als Chagall, Picasso en Mondriaan. Kom langs en laat je inspireren!

{"question":"Could you please tell us until what time you are open tonight?","answer":"Dear Anne Marie,

Thank you for your email. Our appologies for the late answer. However we are open every day from 09.00 am until 18.00 pm depending on how busy it is around 18.00 pm (meaning that whenever it is busy we remain open longer).

Hope that we have informed you sufficiently.

Best regards,

The restaurant has a varied menu that caters to different tastes and dietary preferences.

During my visit, I tried several dishes. The Eggs Florentine was well-prepared, with nicely poached eggs and a good hollandaise sauce. The spinach added a fresh element to the dish. For those looking for a lighter option, the Granola Bowl with Yogurt and fruits is a good choice. The granola had a nice crunch, and the yogurt was creamy. The fruit selection was fresh and added natural sweetness.

The French toast was enjoyable - golden on the outside and soft inside. It wasn't overly sweet, which I appreciated. The freshly squeezed orange juice was a refreshing accompaniment.

Coffee drinkers will find the Americano satisfactory. It was well-brewed and complemented the meal nicely.

What stood out was the quality of ingredients used in the dishes. The food tasted fresh, and it's clear the kitchen pays attention to the details.

The restaurant has a pleasant atmosphere, making it suitable for a relaxed breakfast or brunch. The service was attentive without being intrusive.

If you're in the neighborhood and looking for a good breakfast spot, Bonnie is worth considering.

I'd be happy to return and try more items from their menu. name: Vegan Junk Food Bar
description: Located at Marie Heinekenplein, also known, the Quartier Latin of Amsterdam you will find this awesome restaurant. Close by there are hotspots as The Heineken Brewery and the Albert Cuyp market within a 5-minute walk from the restaurant. Enjoy our #PLANETFRIENDLY #FUTURISTIC and #JUICY takes while sipping on an extraordinary cocktail in a scenery filled with graffiti walls, Hip Hop, R&B music and street art.

name: Restaurant Red
description: Discover the tantalising flavours of the best steak in Amsterdam at Restaurant RED. Gourmet steak lovers, our premium steakhouse provides a dining experience like no other. From succulent ribeye steak to a variety of steak meals, our menu is a carnivore's dream. Not only do we excel at steak, but we're also well-renowned as a top lobster and fish restaurant in Amsterdam. Situated near the historic Rijksmuseum, whether you're looking for breakfast, lunch, dinner, or a canal-side diner, Restaurant RED is the place to be. We promise a dining experience that will keep you coming back for more. Choose Restaurant RED for the ultimate Amsterdam steakhouse experience.

name: Serre
description: Serre restaurant offers a versatile culinary experience within the hotel. Whether it's a morning coffee, a delightful lunch or a leisurely dinner, Serre welcomes you throughout the day. The charming summer terrace offers the perfect backdrop for outdoor dining and afternoon beverages. Led by Chef Bram Postel, Serre proudly holds a Michelin Bib Gourmand, a testament to its commitment to offering high-quality cuisine at moderate prices.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUM3alBqX3VBRRAB","rating":4,"name":"Bianca Jabur","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112122812760604863692?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Nice place and service! I got the afternoon tea with my friend. They forgot to bring a part of it and when I flagged it, we just got a "sorry". I was expecting them to offer to bring it as we paid for that, but it was a sorry only. That is why the experience wasn't 5 stars.","published_at":"5 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-08-13T05:42:28","response_from_owner_text":"Dear Bianca Jabur,

Thank you for visiting Serre Restaurant and for taking the time to share your feedback with us.

We apologize for the oversight with your afternoon tea and understand how disappointing it must have been. We hope that the conversation you had with our Manager addressed your concerns satisfactorily.

We celebrated my girlfriend's birthday at Ron Gastrobar, and I couldn't have asked for a better experience. The team took such great care of us, ensuring everything was discreet and seamless - just what we were hoping for. The food was absolutely delicious, and the staff went above and beyond with their friendly and helpful service.

We also had the chance to try several drinks, and the combinations were spot on - each one unique and well-crafted.

As a sweet touch, they surprised us with a dessert complete with a candle, which made my girlfriend's day even more special. She absolutely loved it!

All in all, it was a fantastic evening, and I highly recommend Ron Gastrobar, be it a special occasion or not. It resembled pancakes more than gnocchi, and I found it unappetizing.

The service was generally good, with an attentive and friendly host. However, there were a few lapses. Despite requesting more several times, it took quite a while to receive it.

Overall, while the service was pleasant, the portions and flavors of the dishes left a lot to be desired. Unfortunately, I wouldn't recommend this experience for the price point (100EU+ per person)

name: Maydanoz
description:
Ontdek de geheimen van de Turkse keuken.Smaken waar je blij van wordt.
Maydanoz is een mediterraan restaurant in Amsterdam waar de Turkse keuken centraal staat, met een menu dat zowel vleesliefhebbers als vegetariers en veganisten aanspreekt.
De gerechten worden bereid met de beste ingredienten en weerspiegelen de rijke diversiteit van de mediterrane keuken.
Van traditionele kebab tot verfijnde vegetarische schotels, bij Maydanoz is er voor elke smaakpapil wel iets te vinden. Uw nieuwe favoriete plek voor tapas in Amsterdam! Onze uitgebreide tapaskaart biedt een heerlijke mix van koude en warme hapjes, geinspireerd op de Turkse en Mediterrane keuken. Deel kleine gerechtjes met vrienden of familie en ontdek de veelzijdigheid van onze smaken.

name: Buffalo Steakhouse
description:
Een gezellig en sfeervol restaurant in Zuid-Amerikaanse stijl.

Vanaf station Rai op 5 minuten loopafstand vindt u ons Buffalo Steakhouse.
Wij zijn gespecialiseerd in het bereiden en serveren van de lekkerste en beste steaks. Om dit voor elkaar te krijgen, halen wij ons vlees uit Argentinie. Het land waar het beste vlees vandaan komt, puur natuur.

Hier leven de runderen voornamelijk op de pampa's; subtropische, natuurlijke graslanden in Zuid-Amerika. De runderen leven zo natuurlijk mogelijk en er wordt geen gebruik gemaakt van groeihormonen. Ze leven hier van verschillende grassoorten.

I had an excellent dining experience. I started with a vada, which was crispy on the outside and soft on the inside, perfectly seasoned and served with a variety of chutneys. (... and order the large!)

Pekelhaarring offers an exceptional dining experience. The ambiance is warm and inviting, making it an ideal spot for any occasion. The service is impeccable--attentive and professional, ensuring every detail is just right. Food is indeed good and honest!

The menu is thoughtfully curated, with each dish showcasing vibrant and well-balanced flavors. This time around, the Tagliatelle with goat stew stands out for its rich, hearty taste, complemented by perfectly cooked pasta.  The Grilled Spring Chicken is equally impressive, tender and flavorful, accompanied by deliciously prepared sides. 

Don't miss the menu of the day specials--they add an extra layer of creativity and delight to the already impressive offerings.  Whether you're a local or visiting, Pekelhaarring promises a refined and memorable dining experience. Highly recommended! name: Ferilli's Specialita UpTown
description: Ferilli's Specialita is located in the heart of Amsterdam's dynamic Zuidas district. It offers an all-day dining experience with authentic Italian brunch, the finest coffee, classic lunch, and aperitivo. The trendy dining experience features DJs on Friday and Saturday nights until late in the evening. The restaurant has a modern and inviting ambiance, attracting sophisticated and fashionable crowds. Every dish is crafted using only the freshest ingredients, sourced directly from Italy or local suppliers. The menu combines traditional Italian recipes with modern culinary techniques. As the night falls, the restaurant transforms into a hotspot with live music, DJs, cocktails, and wines. Ferilli's Specialita is the perfect destination.

name: Maris Piper Brasserie
description:
Maris Piper is a luxurious contemporary brasserie set on a beautiful corner of Frans Halsstraat in the vibrant De Pijp district, South Amsterdam.

Indulge in distinguished dishes from the brasserie menu in a relaxed but classy ambiance, with cosy private booths, an elegant open space, fireplace seating and a luminous conservatory with romantic tables for two.

We walked in (after having tried some other restaurants, but without a reservation on a Friday night...it gets difficult in Amsterdam). We were seated at the bar and gladly took it. At first I felt a bit overlooked, but our waiter quickly realized that and offered us some extra bread on the house. Normally, I wouldn't get excited about bread but the smoked almond/garlic butter they pair it with is just delicious. After a while we were even offered a table seat and continued our dinner there. The food is scrumptious!

The dishes are all prepared with care and were amazing. The wine was surprisingly well-priced and our waiters each gave us amazing warm service. Our waiter Nikos had great recommendations for the food and even for a coffee place in the morning. We felt pampered all evening. I can greatly recommend the smoked eel and foie gras, the scallops and ribeye. Don't forget to order a side of mashed potato with bone marrow- it is really good.

I was even surprised about the desserts; sometimes it can be an afterthought, but at Maris Piper each dessert was well balanced and brought their own personality. This South African micro brewery was an unexpected gem. After finishing the Heineken tour just a short walk away, my wife and I set out to find some local craft beer--and we couldn't have picked a better spot.

We ordered a flight featuring the Cape Point Pilsner, Hazy IPA, Watermelon Wheat, and English Ale. Each beer brought something unique to the table, and all were absolutely fantastic!

Watermelon Wheat (Flagship): Perfectly
balanced, not too sweet, with just the right hint of fruit.

English Ale: A smooth, subtle caramel flavor that felt both rich and light.

Cape Point Pilsner: Surprisingly refreshing; its slightly sour aroma gave way to one of the best pilsners I've ever tasted.

Hazy IPA: An excellent balance of citrusy brightness and just the right amount of bitterness.

While we didn't try the food, if it's even half as good as the beer, it's sure to be a hit. For any beer lover visiting Amsterdam, this spot is a must!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-13T15:06:47","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPiBw-9yIANonFVqMloWw4jKZRpxHwnSsCakPI_=s1024"]}]

One dish that stood out during my visit was the Eggplant tartare, which impressed me with its well-balanced flavors and delightful texture. The salmon, while not reaching the same level as the tartare, was still satisfying, showcasing the freshness of the ingredients.

name: Wils Bakery Cafe
description:
In Wils Bakery Cafe combineren we het ambacht van een bakkerij met de gezelligheid van een Franse bistro. Op de menukaart vind je herkenbare gerechten, bereid met hetzelfde vakmanschap als in restaurant Wils*.
Proef de patisserie van Tania, de gerechten van Koji, lunch met het brood van Maxim en borrel met de wijnen van Barbora. Doe alsof je thuis bent, onze deur staat voor je open.

name: De Pizzabakkers Zuidas
description:
PIZZA & PROSECCO

Pizza
Wij zijn De Pizzabakkers. Onze ambachtelijke pizza's worden gebakken in Italiaanse ovens. Door het complexe deegbereidingsproces is de bodem krokant, dun en vol van smaak. De pizza's worden belegd met uitsluitend verse ingredienten die we zorgvuldig kiezen. Onze worsten en hammen komen van familiebedrijven in Italie. Voor bij de pizza: frisse salades. Voor na de pizza: huisgemaakte Italiaanse toetjes.

Prosecco
Bubbels worden meestal geassocieerd met luxe, maar in Italie is prosecco een pretentieloos drankje. Wij hebben een frizzante en een spumante op de kaart en we maken er lekkere cocktails mee zoals scroppino, hugo en Aperol spritz.

name: Rainbowls Amsterdam
description: Eat the Rainbow! At Rainbowls Amsterdam - Acai | Matcha | Coffee | Juices, we care about healthy food that's not only nutritious but also most delicious. We're open everyday of the week, to serve Amsterdam their beloved coffee, breakfast, brunch, lunch or afternoon snack. Our vegan restaurant and cafe specializes in colourful acai bowls, smoothie bowls, matcha, coffee, juices and more! Swing by our cafe in de Pijp for a good start of the day. Take a seat and relax or pick-up your order on the go!

The decor is pleasant and is no doubt a great place for a couple to have brunch, or take a coffee break from visiting the boutiques surrounding it.

I walked in to have breakfast around 11am on a Monday, and it filled up quickly at around 11.30am. Promptly seated, the service was prompt and pleasant.

Ordered the Eggs Benedict and a cappuccino.

The Eggs benedict was nicely done. Plating was pleasing. The hollandaise sauce was flavourful albeit a tad salty. The poached eggs was done perfectly but I wish either the hollandaise was toned down a little, or the eggs used could have been of a more flavourful variety. The ham was a bit of a let-down, too thin-cut and lacked presence. However, overall the dish is alright.

The cappuccino was OK, but wish the beans had a little more oomph.

Overall, I give the cafe 5 stars. If the food was improved a bit it would be great.","published_at":"a year ago","published_at_date":"2023-09-25T09:34:35","response_from_owner_text":"Dear ,

name: Coffee & Coconuts 'Zuidas'
description:
Aloha,

Some of you might already know us from our location on the Ceintuurbaan in De Pijp.

We are a team of friends and colleagues who strive to create an environment where as soon as you walk in, you feel at home. This is why we roast your coffee in-house with passion, freshly squeeze your OJ every morning, brew your coffee the way you like it, lovingly cook your food and thoughtfully bake your pastries.

We are very excited to have our new location and we truly hope we can make a difference right here in the buzz of the Zuidas. We are very excited to make all your coffees, juices or breaky to go in the morning or during your lunch break, and to serve you in our cafe whenever you want to relax and unwind.

name: BACK
description:
At back we serve freshly prepared meals which you can create yourself using our build your own menu.

At the core of our meals are protein-rich ingredients which are essential in an active lifestyle as they fuel your body's muscle recovery after a good workout but also give you the boost needed after a long day at the office (or a long night ahead).

Besides serving you good food we serve you valuable information. our meal configurator offers you insights in the nutrition information of all our ingredients and even sums them up for the whole meal.

We believe that for food to be tasty, it needs to be fresh, which is why all our ingredients from meats to veggies and juices to dressings are freshly prepared at our restaurant.

Usually, from what I've experienced, the busy moments are between 12pm and 3pm, but afterwards (and in any case with some headphones in/on) you can just chill and focus in a quiet but nice atmosphere.

The toasties, warm drinks and smoothies here are great, and you get a lot for what you pay (my faves are the veggy toastie and dopyaza, together with their delicious chai latte). I also love that they have lots of vegan options - in terms of both drinks and food!

The only minor downside, I would say, is that the type of service is a bit ambiguous - meaning, depending on who is serving that day, it seems as if it is self-service (getting/asking for your own menu and ordering at the counter; also for second orders or when you're finished it looks like they can be a bit slow with paying attention), while it looks like a restaurant that offers table service. However, as mentioned, this isn't always the case.

Despite that, the staff is in any case very nice and friendly. So everyone just goes with the flow eventually, and enjoys their time here!

Hope to you soon!

Have a wonderful day.

name: Doppio Espresso Amsterdam Zuidas
description: Doppio Espresso Zuidas is een verfijnde koffiezaak gelegen in het bruisende zakendistrict van Amsterdam-Zuid. Deze plek is een ware oase voor koffieliefhebbers en heeft een uitstekende reputatie, zoals blijkt uit de overvloed aan positieve Google-recensies. Gasten prijzen de perfect gebrouwen espresso's en cappuccino's, gemaakt door ervaren barista's die echt hun vak verstaan. De sfeer is warm en gastvrij, met een eigentijds interieur dat uitnodigt tot ontspannen en werken. De vriendelijke service krijgt veel lof, en de keuze aan versgebakken lekkernijen en gezonde opties maakt het een ideale plek voor zowel een snelle koffiepauze als een langer verblijf.

We went to Doppio because we desperately needed coffee and for obvious reasons did not trust the in-uni coffee machines.

But this was barely any better. The coffee was burned too hot, the milk foamed too cold, the cookies were packed in plastic and the pizzas (yes don't ask) were microwaved.

If I'm to be fed food that taste like it's being cooked by a student who hadn't quite gotten used to being responsible for their own dinner or ingredient quality -- I would at least like to pay less.

The interior is half way between a gas station, a doner kebab place, and a coffee bar from the 80-ies.

The only redeeming quality was the very kind server, who might not know how to make a good coffee but made up for all of the drabness with a sense of humor and charm

name: Hasta La Vista, Baby - Restaurant & Rooftop Bar
description: Renowned for its beautiful city view, Hasta La Vista, Baby is a high-quality, fast-casual Spanish Rooftop bar and Restaurant in Amsterdam Zuid. With an intimate atmosphere, high quality service and exceptional taste, our Rooftop Restaurant is the perfect setting for lunch, dinner and drinks. Get the best of lunch in Amsterdam Zuid with a city view from the 19th floor of our restaurant on the Zuidas. Enjoy a dinner with excellent Spanish fine dining dishes crafted from the freshest ingredients. By night, the welcoming bar area which includes one of Amsterdams finest Cocktail bars, transforms into a lively hotspot for you to enjoy a wide array of cocktails, wines and spirits. Come over and experience the view yourself or should we say VISTA!

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzekxHU1V3EAE","rating":5,"name":"Monica M.","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113944174080037868402?hl=en-GB","review_text":"I came to this place on my visit to Amsterdam in mid-October 2024.

The first time I visited was in a slight panic trying to find takeaway places to order a quick late night meal that catered for my allergens.  By that point, I'd walked around for about 30 minutes trying to find a place with no luck, until I came to Hearth on 11 Oct 2024.  They'd sadly JUST stopped food service when I arrived, but the lovely owner, Marcus, took pity on my plight and offered some excellent gluten free and vegan quinoa sushi with dressing for free.  I was amazed by his wonderful generosity that I made a point to come and visit to try the menu out properly when my friend from London arrived.

And that we did.  We visited on Sunday 13 October as walk-ins and everything from the food (presentation and flavour) the non-alcoholic cocktails, the ambience, and the service was nothing short of amazing.  Unfortunately Marcus wasn't there the night I visited as a sit-down guest, but I did offer him one promise...this review, so I send my heartfelt gratitude for his kindness and generosity.  He has a wonderful business.  The food was amazing...I couldn't fault the flavours and textures.  Please do yourself a favour and go - you will not be disappointed by the inventiveness of the dishes and drinks at this place.

Thank you again! name: NENI Amsterdam
description: NENI is a vibrant restaurant in Amsterdam that is open from early morning till late at night. It serves an Eastern Mediterranean cuisine, with its rich flavours and abundance of fresh vegetables making it perfectly suitable as a vegetarian restaurant. The table culture at NENI is informal and relaxed, and the service is warm and friendly. The design takes a modern Mediterranean lifestyle with louvre walls, lanterns, fig-trees, and natural materials. The open kitchen in the middle of the restaurant is the eye-catcher that offers diners a good view of how the dishes are prepared.

name: Jiang Nan
description:
A culinary gem in the heart of Amsterdam, offering authentic Chinese cuisine inspired by the flavours of Hangzhou. Experience a serene ambiance that transports you to the picturesque landscapes of the Jiang nan region.

Indulge in a diverse menu featuring signature dishes and vegetarian options, crafted with care by our skilled chefs.

name: Roberto's Restaurant Amsterdam
description: Experience classic Italian gastronomy at Roberto's Restaurant. Pure Italian cuisine inspired by original signature recipes. Roberto's will take you back to the 1960s, when people made dining an event. Our famous Italian restaurant has been a local favourite for over 30 years. Led by Executive Chef Franz Conde, Roberto's offers classic Italian dishes prepared with fresh seasonal ingredients.

name: Guru Restaurant
description: Guru Indian Cuisine, gelegen in Amsterdam, biedt een authentieke Indiase culinaire ervaring. Proef de rijke smaken van India in een sfeervolle omgeving. Geniet van tandoori-grills, smaakvolle curry's en vegetarische opties. Onze attente service en gunstige locatie maken uw bezoek onvergetelijk. Reserveer vandaag nog voor een heerlijke maaltijd bij Guru!

The second I entered, the staff was welcoming and super friendly. When ordering, I decided to go for the mango lassi for drinks, the papri bites and alu tikki for starters, and the butter chicken with a side of garlic nan as a main course. Before my ordered starters, I got a complementary starter with different spicy to sweet sauces and a side of "crackers". After this, I was surprised by the deliciousness of the starters, particularly of the papri bites (would strongly recommend!). The butter chicken was also quite good as the chicken was soft and juicy, the sauce was savory, and it came with some rice which was perfectly made and complemented the dish quite nicely. The side of nan elevated the dish even more in my opinion. Finally, the mango lassi was one of the best ones I have tried in my lifetime so I would strongly recommend to consider ordering it.

Overall, I had a great experience with the staff, the food was quite savory, and I can't wait to go back and try more off the quite varied menu. As for the prices, the main dishes are a bit on the expensive side, however they are worth it as you do get a lot of food and it's quite high quality. name: Impero Romano Amsterdam
description: Enjoy the traditional and original Italian cuisine in Amsterdam at ristorante Impero Romano! Immerse yourself in the Mediterranean atmosphere and taste the real Italy in our restaurant. A large selection of delicious food and wines combined with Italian hospitality and service, is where Impero Romano stands for. This all comes together in a new and beautiful location for both lunch and dinner on Amsteldijk 25.

I enjoy also bake pizzas myself, thanks to my humble culinary background, so I know what a pizza has to be and how is made to obtain certain results.

I will not spend corny words like you see often in the reviews here on Google, but let me say one thing, this is no doubt, easily one of the best pizza I ever had in my life, truly.

The dough is truly amazing, so tasty and delicate, that melts in your mouth after every bite.

Quality-wise, top tier ingredients make this pizza a truly special meal for anyone that wants to try what a modern style Neapolitan pizza means, without flying in Naples.

Bravo to you Dope, I wasn't expecting that much to be honest, I am impressed.

P.s. Next to Dope, there is another pizza place, I am not saying the name, but compared to Dope, it's not worth it, believe me.

name: Mangia Pizza & Wine di Antonio Cavoto
description: Mangia Pizza & Wine da Antonio is an authentic Italian pizzeria that offers real Neapolitan style pizzas prepared with a lot of passion and fresh ingredients in a custom built fired brick oven. We also have starters, salads, desserts, liquors, draft and bottled beers, and a fine selection of wines.

The Service is excellent, starting from a nice welcome by the waiter from the reception. We were there to celebrate our anniversary. The waiter first confirmed our reservation and congrats to us. During the diner, the staff are friendly, checking with us is everything okay, how is the serving speed, would we like to have a chill break before having the dessert etc. Right before we left, the staff congrats us again, really sweet. Our chief is great, she is kind, keep smiling while I cannot imagine how heavy the work she is doing, constantly cooking for us for 3 hours almost.

The Atmosphere is really great too. It has soft lighting, decorated with traditional Japanese style.

Now come to the most important part for me. The FOOD, it is amazing. We chose the Classic menu.
* Started with Tuna tataki (I am too focus on the food and forgot to take picture for it). It has beautifully caramelized crust but super tender inside.
* Then come with Seasalt crusted sea bass. The crust looks interesting too, it looks like puffed pancake, asked the chief, it is 90% salf and 10% whisked egg. The fish filet stays juicy with the Seasalt crust on top. The chief bake the fish skin separately, make it super crispy (I love chips, also fish chips)
* The 3rd course is Canadian lobster with Yuzu garlic butter. Beside those 3 words: lobster + garlic + butter, what do we need to say more. (Spoil alert: it come with the fire show)
* Wagyu steak is definitely the high light of the course. It come with 3 "sauce", himalayan salt, Japanese wasabi and one more (I forgot the name, but that's my favorite match with the Wagyu among all 3) Its provide a bit freshness to compensate well with the grease of Waygu. Btw it come with grilled zucchini and paprika too (I love grilled vegetables!!!!) It also come with some baked Wagyu fat part too. I expect it would be crispy, but the bigger pieces is not crispy enough though (small details)
* The Chicken fried rice served together with the Wagyu. Do not get my wrong, it is tasty too, but having it together with Wagyu, I could not finish it eventually. Personally I am not a fan of having rice together with steam
* The desert: Sazanka pancake (Dorayaki, one my favorite sweets, I love red bean paste ) the Japanese ice cream served with it is Matcha icecream. Personally, I do not like dessert to be too sweet, so leave the syrup aside. The Dorayaki is perfect with Matcha together
* Extra: we also got an extra dessert on the house for the Congratulation","published_at":"5 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-07-22T19:36:43","response_from_owner_text":"Dear Ruiling Zhang,

name: Cucina Casalinga - cucina italiana
description:
Welkom in de authentieke wereld van Cucina Casalinga, het Italiaanse restaurant dat bij de meeste gasten een onvergetelijke ervaring achterlaat.
We zijn verheugd om je kennis te laten maken met de Italiaanse 'hidden gem' van Amsterdam-Zuid, waar de passie voor de Italiaanse thuiskeuken samensmelt met de Italiaanse gastvrijheid om een onvergetelijke culinaire ervaring te creeren.
Wij koken met bijzondere ingredienten uit alle regio's van Italie.
'Duurzaam' en lokaal inkopen zijn belangrijke items bij ons.
Ons verhaal vertellen we in een 4-gangen menu.
Cucina Casalinga is authentiek in een huiselijke setting, daardoor interessant voor 'private dinners': verjaardagen, zakelijke bijeenkomsten, etc.

A presto!
Team Casalinga

What a delightful hidden gem we've found in Amsterdam Zuid! The open kitchen offers a captivating view of the culinary creations being prepared. The service is exceptional, with staff providing detailed explanations of each dish.
* Cornettino con tartara di tonno
This dish consists of a crispy cone filled with tuna tartare. The tuna tartare is delicately seasoned and finely diced, offering a fresh and flavourful experience.
* Panna cotta al porro, uova di aringa, anetto
This features a unique combination of flavours and textures. The "pudding" is made with leeks, giving it a savoury and creamy texture similar to traditional panna cotta but with a savoury twist.
* Cannolicchio siciliano, ricotta, gambero Mazara del vallo
This dish is a mini-Sicilian cannolo filled with creamy ricotta cheese and a shrimp from Mazara del Vallo. The cannolo shell is crispy, while the ricotta is rich and creamy.
* Spaghetto n'duja pistacchio di Bronte, bottarga
The pasta is cooked to perfection, offering a satisfying chewiness. The addition of nduja, a spicy Calabrian sausage paste, provides a unique and bold flavour profile.
* Filetto al pepe verde
This dish features beef tenderloin served with a green peppercorn sauce. The beef is incredibly tender, boasting a rich umami flavour that delights the palate.
* Cake di mandarino con salsa di cioccolato al peperoncino
The cake is infused with the refreshing taste of mandarin, creating a delightful blend of citrus flavours. The addition of the chili-chocolate sauce adds a unique twist, providing a subtle heat that complements the sweetness of the cake.
A big shout-out to Chef @Ceci! I highly recommend paying a visit to Cucina Casalinga for dinner. Cucina Casalinga preserved its hidden charm, offers an authentic Italian experience that left me thoroughly satisfied and yearning for more.

Our experience began with an exclusive seat at the chef's table, a unique setting that allowed for an intimate glimpse into the inner workings of their bustling kitchen. The atmosphere was cozy, comfortable and had an undeniable warmth that matched the personalities of Ces and Alessandra. Every corner was meticulously adorned with tasteful elements that added to the overall charm of the place, making it feel as if you were dining in a traditional Italian home.

Opting for the chef's menu was undoubtedly the best decision. It was a gustatory journey through the regions of Italy, each course meticulously crafted and bursting with flavor. The chefs' passion for their craft was evident in each dish, with every bite telling a story of tradition, innovation, and love for Italian cuisine.

Ces and Alessandra, the masterminds behind the culinary magic, showcased their skills with an effortless grace and a captivating charm. Their commitment to authenticity and quality, along with their dynamic synergy, shone through in every aspect of the dining experience.

Their generosity, too, was apparent, as they surprised us with complimentary drinks. This thoughtful gesture, a testament to their gracious hospitality, added an extra layer of delight to our evening.

In conclusion, this Italian restaurant is a hidden gem that offers a warm, intimate atmosphere and a menu that's nothing short of a symphony of flavors. It's a haven for those who appreciate authentic Italian cuisine and a testament to the talents of Ces and Alessandra. A culinary journey that begins with a warm welcome and ends with a satisfied palate, this restaurant is a must-visit for any food lover in Amsterdam.

name: Osteria Bella Ciao Zuid
description:
Your local Italian Osteria that's all about having good food with a drink or two (or more) with your partner, family and friends.

Located in the two most iconic neighborhoods in Amsterdam, Osteria Bella Ciao it's your authentic modern Osteria with a focus on seasonal and organic italian ingredients.

Our talented Italian chefs are all about delivering a mix of traditional and contemporary dishes respecting each ingredient as our Mamma would do, all served along great and delicious Aperitifs, Italian-Inspired cocktails and of course wines.

Reservations are appreciated but of course walk-ins are more than welcome.

Larger group? Send us and enquire to discover our preset-menus and availability.

name: Tulsi Indian Restaurant
description:
Tulsi Indiaas restaurant is een fine dining Indiaas restaurant gevestigd op Van Woustraat 212, 1073 NA, Amsterdam en Amsterdam Centrum (Nieuwezijds Voorburgwal 34,1012 SB Amsterdam). Wij van hartewelkom om teontspannenkomen, socialis eren en tedelen goede tijden met je familie en vrienden op Tulsi Indian restaurant.

Tulsi restaurant serveer vers bereide authentieke meest populaire Indiase starters zoals Chola Bhatura, Golgappas / PaniPuri, Aloo Tikki, Aloo paprichaat etc. Tulsi restaurant biedtook de verscheidenheid aan andere vegetarisch, niet-vegetarischen tandoori grill gerechten. De gerechten worden bereid door onzeprofessionele chef-koks met meerdan 20 jaar ervaringen .

name: Brasserie Lolita
description: Are you looking for a restaurant in Amsterdam? Look no further than Brasserie Lolita in de Pijp! This gezellig French restaurant is the perfect restaurant in Amsterdam. With delicious French dishes and a cozy atmosphere, it's the perfect spot to enjoy a meal with friends or family. Plus, it's located in the heart of Amsterdam Zuid, de Pijp, making it a great hotspot for all your dining needs. Join for the best dinner or come for some of the best cocktails and have fun at the bar. Brasserie Lolita is well known in Amsterdam and the hotspot for the locals in de Pijp. If you are looking for a French restaurant right in the heart of de Pijp Amsterdam, come check out Brasserie Lolita today! Open till 3am on weekend days.

name: Indian Restaurant Swagat
description: Indiaans Restaurant Swagat is de thuisbasis van authentiek Indisch eten. Swagat is een Sanskriet woord dat staat voor 'welkom'. Bij Indian Restaurant Swagat serveren wij authentiek Indiaans eten gemaakt van echte Indiase kruiden. Onze recepten zullen u een mix van liefde, vreugde, charme, pracht en pith van de Indiase cultuur ervaren. Bij Indiaas Restaurant Swagat mixen we smaak en smaak in een opvallende eet ervaring.

name: Indian Naan | Indian and Nepalese Food Restaurant in Amsterdam
description:
We at Indian Naan are here to satisfy your taste buds by delivering the most delicious food snacks in Amsterdam. We provide the best catering, delivery, and takeaway services (in Bulk) wrapped with authentic Indian and Nepali tastes.

Regardless of your appetite, we provide a large selection of vegetarian, non-vegetarian, and vegan alternatives on our menu. You can sample the delights of vegetables or minced meat by trying our exclusive Momo's menu. With an experienced carrier of 13 years, our experts provide you with the best quality snacks and food.

name: Arles
description:
Arles is a modern bistro located in a quiet side street of the Amsterdamse Pijp. Just like in the Parisian 'bistronomy' scene, you will find creative dishes in an accessible and artistic environment.

 Numa Muller, our chef from Arles, creates a new 4 and 5 course chef's menu every month (a la carte is also possible). His neo-bistro dishes are surprising because of the special combinations of French cuisine with outside influences.

 We have an entirely French wine list with an interesting composition of traditional producers, as well as emerging vins nature.

The restaurant has held a Michelin Bib-Gourmand since 2018.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzby1lTjN3RRAB","rating":4,"name":"Enrico Verdolotti","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104445347436213521651?hl=en-GB","review_text":"The restaurant boasts a beautiful and welcoming atmosphere, paired with excellent service. The staff is professional, friendly, and well-informed, creating an enjoyable dining experience.

However, I was somewhat disappointed with the food, especially considering the price. We opted for the chef's five-course tasting menu, which included three appetizers, one main course, and a dessert.

The first two appetizers were outstanding, the scallop, and the mushrooms in chestnut cream; but the third, a fried croquette, felt uninspired, with the flavor dominated entirely by the frying. The main course, featuring venison, was delicious; however, the addition of two small pieces of eel felt out of place and did not harmonize with the rest of the dish.

The most disappointing aspect, unfortunately, was the dessert. The menu included a pear-based dessert accompanied by parsley ice cream. While innovative, the flavors were peculiar and didn't align with what one would expect for a dessert course. Unsatisfied, I asked to try the second dessert option, which was cottage cheese-based. Sadly, this too failed to impress and did not feel like a fitting conclusion to an otherwise refined meal. For the price I paid I would have expected more.

In summary, while the menu shows great promise, certain elements could be improved. I would strongly recommend revisiting the dessert selection to ensure a more satisfying ending to an otherwise well-thought-out dining experience.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-18T11:51:55","response_from_owner_text":"Hey there, Enrico Verdolotti! name: La Nostra Gigi
description:
Vieni dentro! Waan je in het kloppende jaren 70' hart van Italie in de bruisende Pijp. La Nostra Gigi neemt je mee naar de romantische pleinen en ristoranti van jouw fijnste vakanties in het Zuiden. De plek waar je altijd terecht kunt, voor een snelle espresso macchiato, relaxt glas wijn, feestelijke cocktail of uitgebreid diner. Reserveer een tafel in La Trattoria of kom aanwaaien op het altijd gezellig Terrazza.

'Onze Gigi, het leukste meisje van de Pijp', is die sprankelende, spannende, mooie, wilde, slimme, lieve verrassing die het Marie Heinekenplein siert. Een plek die zich vormt naar de wensen van haar gasten, de plek die jij wilt dat het is. Hier is iedereen uit en thuis! Houd het simpel of pak grandioos uit, alles is hier mogelijk

name: Cannibale Royale Ruysdael
description:
Cannibale Royale, brasserie extraordinaire fulfills all needs for anyone who loves good food, lots of meat, exotic beers and the most beautiful wines. Cannibale Royale is a bar where you can feel like a prehistoric being again. You are always welcome to drop by for a delicious cocktail or special beer to compliment our meaty treats.
Forget all hypes about haute cuisine for a minute, it's time to enjoy everything that is tasteful, rich in flavour and is just simply good.

Un bisou de Cannibale Royale!

We are sorry to hear about the confusion regarding your reservation.
After your contact person filed the request for a group reservation, we sent multiple emails and tried calling him several times to confirm the reservation, but unfortunately, we did not receive any response from him. As a result, we were unable to finalize the reservation and we assumed you were not interested in making the reservation anymore.
Given these efforts to contact your contact person and confirm your reservation, we were quite surprised to see four 1-star reviews from you and your guests. We feel this rating does not reflect the efforts we made to reach out and secure your reservation. We understand your disappointment upon arrival, but we hope you can also see our perspective and reconsider the fairness of these reviews.

We are glad to hear that another restaurant could accommodate you.

Our apologies that you feel this way and that we could not solve this the same night.

name: Restaurant Oud-Zuid
description: Bij Restaurant Oud-Zuid kom je voor puur, origineel eten, een goed glas wijn in een ongedwongen sfeer. We koken volgens onze No-Nonsense filosofie: eten moet goed, lekker en gezond zijn. Daarbij horen alleen 100% natuurlijke en duurzame ingredienten: veel groente, met zorg geselecteerd vlees en dagelijks spartelvers geleverde vis.
